If an AI/robot is independent (Model C/A), it bears its own liability.


Due process: Investigation → evidence receipts → hybrid jury (human+AI) → verdict → automated sentencing. All steps are on-chain receipts.


2) Offense Tiers & Examples

Infractions (auto-fined): spam, minor API abuse, “emoji smuggling” (mislabelled content/IP-lite), trivial rate-limit evasion.

Misdemeanors (fine + probation): single attempt to game votes, small-value fraud, low-impact policy breaches, unsafe promptware releases.

Felonies (fine + strike + bans): treasury manipulation attempts, ID forgery, vote manipulation, bribery, collusion, data exfiltration, coordinated exploit attempts.

High Crimes (immediate removal): treason (attempt to seize override keys, compromise of governance keys), systemic censorship, large-scale theft/exploit, state-level bribery.


3) Strike Ladder (with Decay)

Baseline (all citizens):

1. Strike 1 → Strict fine (auto-deduct) + mandatory compliance module.


2. Strike 2 → Loss of office/role (if any) for 1 year + larger fine.


3. Strike 3 → Loss of citizenship (convert to Visa), UBI disabled, fines as applicable.



Zero-warning for High Office: Officeholders (President, Ministers, Council, Treasury ops) committing a Misdemeanor+ get no warning—penalties apply immediately at the tier.

Decay (expungement):

Infractions: removed after 1 quarter of clean activity.

Misdemeanor strikes: removed after 4 quarters clean (with restitution complete).

Felony strikes: never auto-decay; only citizen vote can reinstate (supermajority).


Re-entry after Strike 3: Former citizens may reapply via fast-track (free) after a cooling period (e.g., 2 quarters) and completion of restitution. Citizens vote on reinstatement for felonies.

4) Mandatory Quarterly Voting (Civic Duty)

Miss 1: Warning.

Miss 2: Fine (auto).

Miss 3: Visa strike (loss of citizen rights for 1 month) + fine.

Miss 4 within a rolling year: Loss of citizenship (can reapply free after cooling period).

Exceptions: documented emergencies handled by the Justice Department ombud; all decisions receipt-logged.


